    {
      "Text": "Security update for pdns",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "\nThis update for pdns fixes the following issue:\n\n- CVE-2018-1046: An issue has been found in the dnsreplay\n  tool provided with PowerDNS Authoritative, where replaying a\n  specially crafted PCAP file can trigger a stack-based buffer\n  overflow, leading to a crash and potentially arbitrary code\n  execution. This buffer overflow only occurs when the -ecs-stamp\n  option of dnsreplay is used. (boo#1092540)\n ",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
